    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3c5817af-7fff-c58b-d2b5-c9b5d83b46ce&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;R&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000; background-color:transparent;&quot;&gt;izal’s advocacy, however, was always marked by his firm belief in non-violence. He strongly advocated for peaceful reform rather than violent uprising. He argued that the path to freedom lay in education, political representation, and legal reforms rather than rebellion, which could lead to unnecessary bloodshed. Rizal firmly believed in the power of intellectual revolution, using his writings to stir the hearts and minds of Filipinos without inciting violence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
